20across%20Iraq%20and%20Syria.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20air%20war%20seriously%20intensified%20the%20following%20year%2C%202017%2C%20with%20an%20average%20of%20around%203%2C300%20bombs%20dropped%20each%20month%20from%20fighter%20jets%20and%20drones.%20May%2C%20June%2C%20and%20July%20all%20saw%20the%20coalition%20release%20over%204%2C000%20weapons%2C%20new%20highs%20during%20Operation%20Inherent%20Resolve.%20But%20that%20August%20saw%20a%20record%205%2C075%20bombs%20dropped%2C%20marking%20the%20only%20time%20that%20figure%20ever%20surpassed%205%2C000.%20The%20intense%20bombing%20coincided%20with%20the%20brutal%20months-long%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.com%2Fnews%2Fworld-middle-east-40271450%5C%22%3EBattle%20of%20Raqqa%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20a%20Syrian%20city%20that%20served%20as%20the%20de-facto%20ISIS%20capital%20in%202014.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BRoughly%20half%20of%20all%20munitions%20dropped%20that%20month%20by%20coalition%20aircraft%20were%20released%20over%20Raqqa%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20RAND%20Corporation%2C%20a%20California-based%20think%20tank%2C%20wrote%20in%20a%202021%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fcontent%2Fdam%2Frand%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRRA300%2FRRA388-1%2FRAND_RRA388-1.pdf%5C%22%3Eanalysis%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20air%20campaign%20against%20ISIS.%20%26quot%3BAlthough%20the%20coalition%20has%20not%20reported%20publicly%20the%20precise%20breakdown%20of%20airframes%20used%20to%20support%20the%20Raqqa%20offensive%2C%20the%20US%20military%20has%20confirmed%20that%20bombers%2C%20fighters%2C%20attack%20aircraft%2C%20and%20RPAs%20were%20all%20employed%20in%20the%20operation%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added%2C%20referring%20to%20remotely%20piloted%20aircraft%2C%20or%20drones.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224852%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20traffic%20roundabout%20in%20the%20city%20of%20Raqqa%2C%20Syria%2C%20Wednesday%2C%20Oct.%2018%2C%202017.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2