20fooled%20a%20whole%20industry%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221440%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Delta%20Air%20Lines%20Technical%20Operations%20facility%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65297e9755f52b01b35f4000%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EUS%20airlines%20have%20been%20flying%20with%20uncertified%20engine%20parts%20for%20years%20after%20a%20London%20distributor%20sold%20fake%20components%20as%20new%20with%20forged%20documentation.%3Cp%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EDistributor%20AOG%20Technics%20is%20accused%20of%20a%20years-long%20scheme%20of%20selling%20fake%20aircraft%20parts%20to%20airlines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EMajor%20US%20airlines%20say%20they%20found%20bogus%20components%20sourced%20from%20the%20company%20on%20their%20CFM56%20engines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EThe%20plot%20involved%20acquiring%20used%20parts%2C%20restoring%20them%2C%20and%20then%20selling%20them%20with%20forged%20paperwork%2C%20according%20to%20legal%20and%20regulatory%20filings.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EGlobal%20airlines%20have%20been%20flying%20with%20fake%20engine%20parts%20for%20years%20%E2%80%94%20and%20the%20industry%20is%20just%20now%20finding%20out.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEarlier%20this%20year%2C%20a%20routine%20inspection%20of%20the%20world's%20best-selling%20jet%20engine%20uncovered%20an%20alarming%20scheme%20involving%20a%20London%20distributor%20called%20AOG%20Technics.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20plot%20was%20uncovered%20at%20TAP%20Air%20Portugal's%20maintenance%20subsidiary%20in%20June%20when%20engineers%20noticed%20one%20of%20the%20%26quot%3Bnew%26quot%3B%20spare%20parts%20for%20a%20CFM56%20engine%20appeared%20older%20than%20what%20the%20paperwork%20indicated%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bloomberg.com%2Fnews%2Ffeatures%2F2023-10-11%2Ffake-parts-found-on-boeing-airbus-jets-plague-airlines%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBloomberg%3C%2Fa%3E%20reported.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20flagged%20the%20inconsistency%20to%20French%20manufacturer%20Safran%2C%20which%20co-produces%20the%20CFM56%20with%20General%20Electric%20as%20a%2050%2F50%20joint%20venture%20called%20CFM%20International.%C2%A0The%20engine%20is%20used%20on%20Airbus%20and%20Boeing%20planes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESafran%20confirmed%20the%20fraudulent%20documentation%2C%20launching%20an%20investigation%20that%20found%20thousands%20of%20parts%20across%20at%20least%20126%20CFM56%20engines%20were%20sold%20without%20a%20legitimate%20airworthiness%20certificate.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20European%20Union%20Aviation%20Safety%20Agency%20confirmed%20the%20bogus%20parts%20in%20an%20August%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.easa.europa.eu%2Fen%2Fdomains%2Faircraft-products%2Fsuspected-unapproved-parts%2Faircraft-parts-distributed-aog-technics%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eregulatory%20filing%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20agency%20quickly%20warned%20operators%2C%20shops%2C%20and%20distributors%20to%20check%20their%20records%20of%20CFM56%20parts%20supplied%20from%20AOG%20and%20remove%20any%20in%20use.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECarriers%20including%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Funlawful-parts-found-in-planes-southwest-american-airlines-united-airlines-2023-9%23%3A~%3Atext%3DThree%2520US%2520airlines%2520found%2520illegitimate%2CSouthwest%252C%2520United%252C%2520and%2520American.%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EUnited%2C%20Southwest%2C%20Delta%2C%20and%20American%20have%20all%20since%20identified%20illegitimate%20parts%20flying%20on%20their%20passenger%20jetliners%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAmerican%2C%20Delta%2C%20and%20Southwest%20told%20Insider%20that%20a%20small%20number%20of%20aircraft%20contained%20the%20falsified%20parts%2C%20and%20each%20has%20been%20taken%20out%20of%20service%20for%20replacement.%20United%20confirmed%20the%20same%20in%20September%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-airlines-is-third-carrier-affected-by-suspect-engine-parts-2023-9%3F_gl%3D1*5om7y9*_ga*MjgzODQ4NTE2LjE2ODA3MTMzMTA.*_ga_E21CV80ZCZ*MTY5NzIyMDc1OC4xMDIuMS4xNjk3MjIwNzcwLjQ4LjAuMA..%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Erevealing%20it%20found%20fake%20parts%20on%20its%20planes.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECFM%20itself%20also%20fell%20victim%20to%20the%20plot%20after%20buying%20parts%20from%20AOG%20indirectly%20and%20using%20them%20on%20its%20engines%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Fjet-engine-maker-cfm-says-suspect-parts-found-its-own-repair-shops-2023-10-04%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20engine%20maker%20filed%20a%20lawsuit%20against%20AOG%20in%20September%2C%20and%20the%20distributor%20has%20since%20submitted%20documents%20detailing%20its%20sales%20history%20after%20being%20ordered%20to%20by%20a%20London%20judge%2C%20according%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Fbusiness%2Fairlines%2Fdodgy-jet-parts-ge-boeing-plane-engines-a3fcbcfd%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EWall%20Street%20Journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAn%20attorney%20for%20CFM%20International%20told%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reuters.com%2Fbusiness%2Faerospace-defense%2Fengine-maker-cfm-says-up-96-planes-affected-by-fake-parts-probe-2023-09-20%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EReuters%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20AOG%20Technics%20had%20created%20a%20%26quot%3Bdeliberate%2C%20dishonest%2C%20and%20sophisticated%20scheme%20to%20deceive%20the%20market%20with%20falsified%20documents%20on%20an%20industrial%20scale.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENone%20of%20the%20AOG-supplied%20parts%20have%20a%20strict%20lifespan%20in%20which%20they%20must%20be%20replaced%20after%20a%20certain%20number%20of%20flights%2C%20Bloomberg%20reported.%C2%A0But%20the%20scandal%20could%20potentially%20impact%20safety%20as%20it's%20impossible%20to%20know%20how%20uncertified%20parts%20will%20hold%20up%20in%20extreme%20conditions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20example%2C%20uncertified%20bolts%20and%20brackets%20caused%20a%20Convair%20CV-580%20turboprop%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.baaa-acro.com%2Fcrash%2Fcrash-convair-cv-580-hirtshals-55-killed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ecrash%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20Europe%20in%201989%2C%20killing%2055%20people.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHow%20to%20fool%20an%20airline%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20companies%20scramble%20to%20find%20the%20fake%20parts%2C%20investigators%20are%20trying%20to%20figure%20out%20how%20the%20scheme%20happened.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAOG%20was%20founded%20eight%20years%20ago%20by%20entrepreneur%20Jose%20Alejandro%20Zamora%20Yrala%2C%20according%20to%20the%20WSJ.%20The%20company%20operated%20as%20a%20middleman%20between%20engine%20shops.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Bloomberg%2C%20the%20company%20started%20the%20scheme%20as%20far%20back%20as%202018%2C%20acquiring%20used%20parts%20that%20would%20then%20be%20restored%20and%20sold%20with%20fraudulent%20documentation%20%E2%80%94%20including%20forged%20signatures%20%E2%80%94that%20indicated%20they%20were%20fresh%20from%20the%20factory.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20isn't%20a%20new%20strategy.%20The%20Federal%20Aviation%20Administration%20launched%20a%20voluntary%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.faa.gov%2Fdocumentlibrary%2Fmedia%2Fadvisory_circular%2Fac00-56a.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaudit%3C%2Fa%3E%20program%20for%20suppliers%20after%20some%20120%20convictions%20involving%20fake%20parts%20were%20made%20between%201990%20and%201996.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20FAA%20program%20helps%20accredit%20sellers%20without%20using%20agency%20resources%2C%20but%20the%20lack%20of%20oversight%20opens%20a%20hole%20that%20third-party%20sellers%20like%20AOG%20can%20exploit%20%E2%80%94%20especially%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Funited-hiring-7000-mechanics-amid-technician-shortage-could-impact-operations-2023-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eindustry%20continues%20to%20face%20staffing%20and%20part%20shortages%3C%2Fa%3E%20amid%20the%20post-pandemic%20travel%20boom.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20were%20busting%20people%20and%20sending%20them%20to%20prison%2020%20years%20ago%20for%20this%2C%26quot%3B%20former%20Department%20of%20Transportation%20Inspector%20General%20Mary%20Schiavo%20told%20Bloomberg.%20%26quot%3BIt's%20the%20same%20old%20scheme.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscammer-fooled-us-airlines-by-selling-fake-engine-parts-filings-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697226246000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65297e7f68f1d46f52b16095%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscammer-fooled-us-airlines-by-selling-fake-engine-parts-filings-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20scammer%20has%20been%20selling%20fake%20engine%20parts%20to%20airlines%20in%20a%20years-long%20scheme%20that%20caused%20US%20carriers%20to%20fly%20planes%20with%20uncertified%20components%2C%20filings%20say.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22trains%40insider.com%20(Taylor%20Rains)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A27%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscammer-fooled-us-airlines-by-selling-fake-engine-parts-filings-2023-10%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Prominent%20bankruptcy%20judge%20David%20Jones%20recused%20from%20cases%2C%20under%20investigation%20after%20exposure%20of%20undisclosed%20romantic%20relationship%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20interior%20of%20a%20Texas%20courthouse%2C%20with%20US%20and%20Texas%20flags%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65299a2f55f52b01b35f7d7f%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22420%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20in%20Houston%2C%20where%20Judge%20David%20Jones%20presides.%3Cp%3EUS%20District%20%26amp%3B%20Bankruptcy%20Court%2C%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%20%3Cli%3ELast%20week%2C%20Insider%20revealed%20that%20prominent%20bankruptcy%20judge%20David%20Jones%20was%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20a%20bankruptcy%20attorney.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EToday%2C%20he%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20his%20cases%20and%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20has%20opened%20an%20investigation.%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3Cli%3EThe%20Office%20of%20the%20US%20Trustee%2C%20the%20bankruptcy%20regulator%2C%20has%20filed%20an%20objection%20in%20the%20Corizon%20bankruptcy%20case%2C%20citing%20Jones'%20%26quot%3Badmissions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fli%3E%20%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EDavid%20Jones%2C%20the%20chief%20bankruptcy%20judge%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%2C%20has%20requested%20to%20be%20reassigned%20from%20his%20cases%20%E2%80%94%20a%20week%20after%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprison-health-provider-corizon-bankruptcy-clouded-by-judge-romantic-relationship-2023-10%5C%22%3EInsider%20broke%20the%20news%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20he%20was%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20with%20Elizabeth%20Freeman%2C%20a%20prominent%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20attorney.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20is%20now%20under%20investigation%2C%20according%20to%20audio%20from%20a%20hearing%20today%20in%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAs%20you%20all%20know%20I%20have%20been%20the%20subject%20of%20a%20fair%20amount%20of%20media%20attention%20over%20the%20past%20week%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20told%20the%20court.%20%26quot%3BThat%20media%20attention%20has%20prompted%20an%20investigation%20by%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit%20in%20doing%20their%20statutory%20duties.%20That%20investigation%20is%20ongoing.%26quot%3B%20He%20goes%20on%20to%20say%20that%20he%20voluntarily%20agreed%20to%20be%20removed%20from%20his%20cases%20%26quot%3Bpending%20the%20outcome%20of%20that%20investigation.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%20data-embed-type%3D%5C%22raw%5C%22%20data-type%3D%5C%22embed%5C%22%3E%3Ciframe%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.jwplayer.com%2Fplayers%2FaqVW72lZ-FccwB2ub.html%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Judge%20David%20Jones%20addresses%20the%20US%20Bankruptcy%20Court%20for%20the%20Southern%20District%20of%20Texas%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22100%25%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3Cp%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20representative%20of%20the%20Fifth%20Circuit's%20executive%20office%20declined%20to%20comment%20when%20asked%20about%20the%20investigation.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20and%20Freeman%20were%20both%20players%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcorizon-health-bankruptcy-yescare-texas-two-step-law-2023-8%5C%22%3Econtroversial%20bankruptcy%20case%3C%2Fa%3E%20involving%20a%20leading%20private%20prison%20healthcare%20provider%2C%20Corizon.%20Corizon%20split%20last%20year%20in%20a%20maneuver%20known%20as%20the%20Texas%20Two-Step%2C%20giving%20one%20company%2C%20YesCare%2C%20all%20the%20active%20prison%20contracts%20and%20saddling%20the%20other%2C%20Tehum%20Care%20Services%2C%20with%20most%20of%20Corizon's%20debt.%20Tehum%20was%20then%20filed%20into%20bankruptcy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20oversaw%20settlement%20talks%20in%20that%20bankruptcy%2C%20helping%20Tehum%20and%20a%20committee%20of%20creditors%20reach%20a%20%2437%20million%20proposed%20settlement%20deal%20that%20would%20protect%20most%20of%20YesCare's%20assets%2C%20which%20court%20filings%20indicate%20total%20more%20than%20%24173%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%20represented%20YesCare%20in%20those%20talks.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFreeman%2C%20Jones'%20former%20clerk%20and%20a%20former%20partner%20at%20Jackson%20Walker%2C%20signed%20off%20on%20Jones'%20appointment%20as%20mediator%20in%20May%2C%20according%20to%20a%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kccllc.net%2Ftehum%2Fdocument%2F2390086230522000000000041%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estipulation%20and%20agreed%20order%3C%2Fa%3E%20submitted%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20docket.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENeither%20party%20acknowledged%20their%20relationship%20at%20the%20time.%20Allegations%20of%20the%20relationship%20first%20surfaced%20in%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24018713-michael-van-deelen-complaint%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20suit%3C%2Fa%3E%20filed%20last%20week%20by%20Michael%20Van%20Deelen%2C%20a%20pro%20se%20plaintiff%20who%20shared%20the%20complaint%20with%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20did%20not%20respond%20to%20Insider's%20queries%20for%20that%20story.%20But%20he%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fbankruptcy-judge-jones-named-in-a-lawsuit-over-romantic-relationship-with-local-lawyer-71df2c00%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Elater%20confirmed%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20that%20he%20and%20Freeman%20are%20in%20a%20romantic%20relationship%20and%20have%20shared%20a%20home%20for%20years.%20He%20said%20he%20didn't%20believe%20he%20had%20a%20duty%20to%20disclose%20because%20they%20aren't%20married%20and%20he%20didn't%20benefit%20economically%20from%20her%20legal%20work.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20said%20he'd%20only%20have%20to%20recuse%20himself%20from%20cases%20in%20which%20Freeman%20was%20appearing%20if%20they%20were%20married%20and%20owned%20communal%20property.%20He%20told%20the%20Journal%20that%20wasn't%20the%20case.%20He%20said%20he%20owns%20the%20Houston%20home%20that%20Freeman%20resides%20in%2C%20and%20he%20pays%20the%20home's%20utilities.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20quick%20search%20by%20Insider%20of%20Harris%20County's%20property%20records%20casts%20doubt%20on%20that%20assertion.%20A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.documentcloud.org%2Fdocuments%2F24032507-general-warranty-deed%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Edeed%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20their%20home%20lists%20Jones%20and%20Freeman%20as%20joint%20owners.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20order%20submitted%20earlier%20today%2C%20marked%20%26quot%3Beffective%20on%20entry%2C%26quot%3B%20Jones%20requests%20to%20be%20reassigned%20from%20the%20complex%20cases%20and%20related%20proceedings%20assigned%20to%20him.%20Those%20cases%20will%20be%20reassigned%20to%20the%20two%20other%20bankruptcy%20judges%20in%20the%20court%20%E2%80%94%20Marvin%20Isgur%20and%20Christopher%20Lopez.%20(The%20Wall%20Street%20Journal%20was%20the%20first%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wsj.com%2Farticles%2Fbankruptcy-judge-jones-to-stop-handling-complex-cases-after-relationship-with-lawyer-revealed-fad88b0c%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0Jones'%20recusal.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELopez%20is%20the%20judge%20overseeing%20the%20Tehum%20bankruptcy%3B%20in%20May%2C%20he%20appointed%20Jones%20to%20act%20as%20mediator%20in%20the%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJones%20did%20not%20immediately%20respond%20to%20requests%20for%20comment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Office%20of%20the%20US%20Trustee%20intervenes%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EToday%20the%20Office%20of%20the%20US%20Trustee%2C%20the%20federal%20regulator%20that%20oversees%20bankruptcy%20cases%2C%20took%20the%20unusual%20step%20of%20intervening%20in%20the%20bankruptcy%20case.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20office%20filed%20multiple%20objections%20to%20the%20proposed%20settlement%20plan%20overseen%20by%20Judge%20Jones%2C%20including%20concerns%20about%20Jones'%20role%20as%20mediator.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20plan%2C%20released%20on%20September%2029%2C%20would%20resolve%20more%20than%20%241.2%20billion%20in%20Corizon%20debts%2C%20including%20tens%20of%20millions%20of%20dollars%20in%20unpaid%20invoices%20and%20hundreds%20of%20malpractice%20suits%20filed%20by%20prisoners%20and%20their%20families%20who%20have%20alleged%20negligent%20care.%20The%20deal%20would%20offer%20the%20malpractice%20claimants%20%E2%80%94%20even%20families%20suing%20on%20behalf%20of%20loved%20ones%20who%20they%20say%20died%20due%20to%20Corizon's%20neglect%20%E2%80%94%20just%20%245%2C000%20each.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHector%20Garcia%20Jr.%2C%20the%20son%20of%20Hector%20Garcia%2C%20who%20died%20in%20August%202019%20at%20the%20age%20of%2055%20after%20his%20perforated%20ulcer%20was%20left%20untreated%20by%20Corizon%20at%20a%20New%20Mexico%20jail%2C%20called%20the%20%245%2C000%20%26quot%3Ba%20slap%20in%20the%20face.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trustee's%20office%20specifically%20references%20Jones%2C%20writing%20that%20%26quot%3Brecent%20admissions%20by%20the%20judicial%20mediator%20may%20raise%20issues%20about%20the%20propriety%20of%20the%20mediation%20that%20serves%20as%20the%20basis%20for%20this%20global%20settlement%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20the%20very%20propriety%20of%20the%20settlement%20and%20plan%20itself.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trustee's%20office%20also%20objected%20in%20a%20variety%20of%20ways%20to%20the%20treatment%20of%20the%20imprisoned%20malpractice%20claimants.%20The%20objection%20says%20plan%20fails%20to%20outline%20creditor%20options%20in%20%26quot%3Bplain%20English%26quot%3B%20and%20fails%20to%20justify%20setting%20aside%20so%20little%20funds%20for%20the%20claims%20by%20current%20and%20former%20prisoners.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20bankruptcy%20plan%20breaks%20creditors%20down%20into%20several%20classes.%20The%20largest%20is%20the%20medical%20malpractice%20claimants%2C%20who%20collectively%20say%20they're%20owed%20almost%20%241.1%20billion.%20Claims%20by%20a%20class%20composed%20of%20vendors%20such%20as%20hospitals%20amount%20to%20far%20less%20%E2%80%94%20around%20%24111%20million.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20plan%20proposes%20giving%20the%20malpractice%20claimants%20only%20around%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20total%20settlement.%20The%20trustee's%20objection%20raises%20questions%20about%20this%20%26quot%3Bdivision%20of%20the%20proceeds%26quot%3B%20and%20the%20plan's%20failure%20to%20explain%20why%20those%20%241.1%20billion%20in%20claims%20would%20effectively%20be%20reduced%20by%20up%20to%2097%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20trustee's%20office%20also%20objected%20to%20a%20lack%20of%20information%20regarding%20malpractice%20plaintiffs%20who%20reject%20the%20%245%2C000%20payout%20offer.%20%26quot%3BCreditors%20who%20opt%20out%20will%20be%20left%20to%20recover%20from%20a%20barren%20estate%2C%20one%20that%20was%20stripped%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20objection%20reads%2C%20%26quot%3Bof%20all%20of%20its%20valuable%20assets%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20combination%20and%20divisional%20mergers%20that%20occurred%20prior%20to%20the%20bankruptcy%20filing.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20other%20words%2C%20Corizon's%20Texas%20Two-Step.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EResearch%20assistance%3A%20Lila%20Hassan.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprominent-bankruptcy-judge-recused-under-investigation-after-undisclosed-romantic-relationship-exposed-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697225881000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652992e355f52b01b35f6e29%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fprominent-bankruptcy-judge-recused-under-investigation-after-undisclosed-romantic-relationship-exposed-2023-10%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20order%2C%20filed%20today%2C%20comes%20after%20Insider%20first%20reported%20on%20the%20relationship%20between%20Jones%20and%20a%20prominent%20Texas%20bankruptcy%20attorney.%20Meanwhile%2C%20the%20US%20Trustee's%20Office%20has%20filed%20an%20objection%20in%20the%20Corizon%20bankruptcy%2C%20citing%20Jones'%20%26quot%3Brecent%2