C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20NASA%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20woman%20stands%20in%20front%20of%20a%20large%20screen%20displaying%20images%20from%20the%20asteroid%20Bennu%20at%20a%20NASA%20press%20conference%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6529903368f1d46f52b18989%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ESome%20of%20the%20sample%20matter%20OSIRIS-REx%20collected%20from%20the%20asteroid%20Bennu%2C%20shown%20during%20a%20press%20conference.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EA%203D%20computer%20model%20of%20one%20of%20the%20particles%20showed%20it%20contained%20a%20large%20amount%20of%20carbon%20and%20evidence%20of%20water.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20it's%20not%20liquid%20water%2C%20said%20Dworkin.%20The%20water%20is%20trapped%20in%20minerals.%20%26quot%3BScientists%20will%20also%20be%20searching%20for%20tiny%20pools%20of%20water%20trapped%20inside%20mineral%20grains%20such%20as%20have%20been%20found%20in%20some%20meteorites%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EWhat%20does%20the%20asteroid%20sample%20look%20like%3F%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20sample%20is%20black%20and%20rocky.%20The%20color%20is%20likely%20a%20result%20of%20the%20high%20abundance%20of%20carbon%20and%20the%20mineral%20magnetite%2C%20Dworkin%20said.%20Both%20are%20found%20on%20Earth%2C%20too.%20Magnetite%20is%20very%20plentiful%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsoilsfacstaff.cals.wisc.edu%2Ffacstaff%2Fbarak%2Fvirtual_museum%2Fmagnetite%2Fmagnetite_tx.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epresent%20in%3C%2Fa%3E%20many%20types%20of%20rocks.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDworkin%20can't%20say%20for%20sure%20yet%20what%20the%20texture%20is%20like.%20%26quot%3BSo%20far%20only%20fine%20particles%2C%20the%20size%20of%20sand%20or%20smaller%2C%20have%20been%20handled%20carefully%20with%20tweezers%20to%20prevent%20contamination%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%20They're%20doing%20all%20the%20analysis%20in%20clean%20rooms%20at%20NASA's%20Johnson%20Space%20Center%20in%20Houston%2C%20Texas.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Black%20rocks%20from%20the%20asteroid%20Bennu%20on%20OSIRIS-REx's%20sample%20collector%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F652991096561dd877e7a7b76%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EA%20close-up%20image%20of%20the%20OSIRIS-REx%20sample%20shown%20on%20a%20screen%20during%20a%20press%20conference%20at%20the%20Johnson%20Space%20Center%20in%20Houston%2C%20Texas.%3Cp%3EMark%20Felix%2FAFP%20via%20Getty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20they've%20weighed%20a%20few%20particles%2C%20the%20team%20is%20waiting%20on%20detailed%20density%20measurements%2C%20which%20they'll%20perform%20next%20month.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20would%20expect%20samples%20to%20be%20a%20little%20less%20dense%20than%20an%20average%20rock%20and%20denser%20than%20ice%2C%26quot%3B%20Dworkin%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20more%20will%20scientists%20learn%20from%20the%20Bennu%20sample%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EDworkin%20said%20the%20OSIRIS-REx%20team%20has%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Farxiv.org%2Fpdf%2F2308.11794.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E12%20major%20hypotheses%3C%2Fa%3E%20about%20the%20sample.%20They%20want%20to%20further%20analyze%20it%20and%20interpret%20the%20findings%20so%20far%20of%20the%20magnetite%2C%20clay%2C%20carbonate%2C%20water%2C%20and%20other%20minerals.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20information%20will%20help%20them%20look%20for%20organic%20compounds%20necessary%20for%20life.%20The%20sample%20will%20also%20provide%20clues%20about%20the%20history%20of%20the%20solar%20system.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221999%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Two%20people%20in%20blue%20protective%20gear%20and%20white%20gloves%20use%20tools%20on%20the%20container%20holding%20the%20Bennu%20asteroid%20sample%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65298cc255f52b01b35f6017%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EAstromaterials%20processors%20Mari%20Montoya%2C%20left%2C%20and%20Curtis%20Calva%2C%20right%2C%20collect%20asteroid%20particles%20from%20the%20base%20of%20the%20OSIRIS-REx%20science%20canister.%3Cp%3ENASA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ENASA%20is%20sending%20portions%20of%20the%20regolith%20to%20other%20institutions%20all%20over%20the%20world%20but%20also%20preserving%20much%20of%20it%20for%20future%20research.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BMy%20greatest%20hope%20is%20that%20future%20generations%20of%20scientists%20will%20learn%20things%20I%20cannot%20imagine%20with%20new%20techniques%20and%20new%20ideas%20with%20the%2070%25%20of%20the%20sample%20that%20will%20be%20available%20for%20the%20future%2C%26quot%3B%20Dworkin%20said.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUntil%20then%2C%20the%20team%20expects%20to%20learn%20much%20more%20in%20the%20coming%20weeks%2C%20months%2C%20and%20years.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20results%20aren't%20even%20the%20appetizer%20yet%2C%20just%20the%20enticing%20scent%20coming%20from%20the%20kitchen%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Dworkin.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20main%20course%20is%20on%20the%20way%20and%20we%20have%20every%20reason%20to%20believe%20it%20will%20be%20spectacular.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fbennu-asteroid-sample-photos-nasa-carbon-water-osiris-rex-2023-10%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697224726000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65298b9268f1d46f52b17f31%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2