bstained%20from%20voting%20on%20a%20resolution%20moved%20in%20the%20United%20Nations%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20(UNHRC)%20that%20extended%20by%20a%20year%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20independent%20expert%20documenting%20the%20human%20rights%20situation%20in%20Russia.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20has%20abstained%20from%20all%20resolutions%20moved%20against%20Russia%20in%20the%20UN%20since%20the%20Ukraine%20war%20in%20February%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftwitter.com%2FUN_HRC%2Fstatus%2F1712475823192907897%3Ft%3DpOjN0tVlxMpc_e2XeXA8lA%26s%3D19%5C%22%3Eresolution%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20adopted%20on%20Thursday%20at%20the%20UNHRC%E2%80%99s%2054th%20regular%20session%2C%20with%2018%20votes%20in%20favour%20and%20seven%20against.%20Like%20earlier%2C%20the%20number%20of%20abstentions%20this%20time%20around%20were%20also%20more%20than%20the%20number%20of%20votes%20in%20favour%20of%20the%20resolution.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20resolution%20extended%20the%20Special%20Rapporteur%E2%80%99s%20mandate%2C%20urging%20Russia%20to%20comply%20with%20all%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20obligations%20under%20international%20human%20rights%20law.%20The%20UNHRC%20previously%20appointed%20a%20Commission%20of%20Inquiry%20to%20look%20into%20rights%20abuses%20related%20to%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBolivia%2C%20China%2C%20Cuba%2C%20Eritrea%2C%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Kyrgyzstan%2C%20and%20Vietnam%20voted%20against%20the%20resolution.%20Along%20with%20India%2C%20the%20United%20Arab%20Emirates%2C%20South%20Africa%2C%20Mexico%2C%20Bangladesh%2C%20Maldives%2C%20and%20Morocco%20abstained%20from%20the%20voting.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20also%20abstained%20from%20last%20year%E2%80%99s%20resolution%2C%20as%20it%20has%20with%20regard%20to%20all%20resolutions%20criticising%20Russia%20for%20the%20invasion%20of%20Ukraine%20in%20February%202022.%20New%20Delhi%20has%20refrained%20from%20directly%20blaming%20Russia%20but%20called%20for%20a%20peaceful%20resolution%20and%20to%20stop%20targeting%20civilians.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EContrary%20to%20the%20stance%20taken%20by%20the%20West%2C%20India%20has%20increased%20the%20purchase%20of%20Russian%20crude%20oil%2C%20arguing%20that%20it%20is%20necessary%20to%20ameliorate%20the%20economic%20consequence%20of%20the%20Ukraine%20war.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20latest%20resolution%20urged%20Russia%20to%20ensure%20fundamental%20freedoms%2C%20including%20those%20of%20thought%2C%20opinion%20and%20expression%2C%20and%20peaceful%20assembly%2C%20%E2%80%9Cin%20particular%20by%20removing%20restrictions%20on%20diversity%20in%20ideas%2C%20criticism%20and%20dissent%20as%20well%20as%20associated%20rights%20to%20liberty%20and%20security%20of%20person%2C%20fair%20trial%2C%20and%20freedom%20from%20torture%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20vote%20came%20after%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20bid%20to%20rejoin%20the%20Council%20was%20rejected%20by%20the%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20on%20Tuesday%2C%20October%2010.%20Russia%20had%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fas-un-votes-to-remove-russia-from-unhrc-india-abstains%5C%22%3Eexpelled%3C%2Fa%3E%20from%20the%20UNHRC%20in%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1697204709000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2021%2F03%2F23142706%2F5553604787_a38f04d388_k1.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-abstain-unhrc-vote-extend-term-special-rapporteur-russia%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20United%20Nations%20Human%20Rights%20Council%20resolution%20extended%20by%20a%20year%20the%20mandate%20of%20the%20independent%20expert%20documenting%20the%20human%20rights%20situation%20in%20Russia.%C2%A0%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fdiplomacy%2Findia-abstain-unhrc-vote-extend-term-special-rapporteur-russia%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Coca-Cola%20India's%2