Registration%20Board%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2Fsupreme-court-hearing-plea-seeking-comprehensive-guidelines-for-safe-ethical-advertising-corporate-hospitals-239942%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20petitioner%2C%20Aniruddha%20Narayan%20Malpani%2C%20said%20that%20physicians%20working%20in%20corporate%20hospitals%20are%20unfairly%20advantaged%20due%20to%20a%20loophole%20that%20allows%20corporate%20hospitals%20to%20advertise%20themselves%20but%20not%20individual%20doctors.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwbconsumers.gov.in%2Fwritereaddata%2FACT%2520%26amp%3B%2520RULES%2FRelevant%2520Act%2520%26amp%3B%2520Rules%2FCode%2520of%2520Medical%2520Ethics%2520Regulations.pdf%5C%22%3ERegulations%3C%2Fa%3E%20under%20the%20National%20Medical%20Commission%20Act%2C%202019%20prohibit%20doctors%20from%20advertising%20themselves%20or%20soliciting%20patients.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EBut%20corporate%20hospitals%20don%E2%80%99t%20fall%20under%20the%20remit%20of%20the%20NMC%20Act%2C%C2%A0%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6%20This%20dichotomy%20results%20in%20a%20situation%20wherein%20the%20%5BNMC%5D%20possesses%20limited%20to%20no%20authority%20over%20the%20advertising%20strategies%20employed%20by%20corporate%20hospitals%2C%E2%80%9D%20Malpani%E2%80%99s%20petition%20said%20according%20to%20%3Cem%3ELiveLaw%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIt%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThus%2C%20it%20becomes%20evident%20that%2C%20despite%20the%20uniform%20application%20of%20the%20Ethics%20Regulations%20of%202002%20to%20all%20physicians%20without%20discrimination%2C%20those%20in%20association%20with%20hospitals%20are%20unfairly%20advantaged%20due%20to%20the%20advertising%20tactics%20employed%20by%20hospitals.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHe%20went%20on%20to%20argue%20that%20this%20unfair%20advantage%20was%20making%20healthcare%20less%20affordable%20to%20the%20bulk%20of